<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!--
    How to add a new language:
    1. Create a new directory: res/values-{qualifier}/strings.xml
       See examples: https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/app-languages#sample-config
    2. Copy this file as a starting template.
    3. Translate each <string> value (keep the name attribute unchanged).
    4. Register the locale in res/xml/locales_config.xml:
         <locale android:name="{BCP 47 tag}" />
    5. Add the resource qualifier to resourceConfigurations in app/build.gradle.kts:
         androidResources {
            localeFilters += setOf("en", "{new qualifier}")
        }
    6. Strings that should NOT be translated (e.g. brand names like "ViPER4Android")
       can be deleted from this file, the default English value will be used.
-->
